&lt;h2&gt;Tip Number Two: Current¬†View&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This shortcut is quite similar to the previous one, but it is used in the view debugger. So let‚Äôs say you start a view debugger and you‚Äôd like to know where exactly in the view‚Äôs hierarchy the currently highlighted view is or what its constraints are. And since views in the view debugger are just named by its main class (eg. UIButton), it is really not easy to find it. Xcode shortcuts to the rescue! Just click the view your heart desires and hit ‚åò+‚áß+D. Easy!&lt;/p&gt;
